sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE, HOMESTEAD, COURTYARD - LATE DAY
quote: I'm Anakin Skywalker. I'm here looking for my mother.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE, HOMESTEAD, COURTYARD - LATE DAY
quote: Is my mother here?

sceneTitle: INT. TATOOINE, HOMESTEAD, DINING AREA - LATE DAY
quote: To find my mother.

sceneTitle: INT. TATOOINE, HOMESTEAD, DINING AREA - LATE DAY
quote: I can feel her pain, and I will find her. I know she's alive.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE, HOMESTEAD, MOISTURE FARM - LATE DAY
quote: You are going to have to stay here. These are good people, Padme. You'll be safe.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE, HOMESTEAD, MOISTURE FARM - LATE DAY
quote: I trust you'll watch over her, Owen.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE, HOMESTEAD, MOISTURE FARM - LATE DAY
quote: I won't be long.

sceneTitle: INT. COCKPIT, FETT SHIP, SPACE, GEONOSIS
quote: Nearly there, son.

sceneTitle: INT. COCKPIT, FETT SHIP, SPACE, GEONOSIS
quote: Dad, look!!

sceneTitle: INT. COCKPIT, FETT SHIP, SPACE, GEONOSIS
quote: Hang on!
Dad! Watch out!
Stay calm, son. We'll be fine. That Jedi won't be able to follow us through this.
Got him! Yeahhhhh!
We won't see him again.
Mom... Mom... Mom...
Annie...? Is it you?
I�m here, Mom. You�re safe. Hang on. I�m going to get you out of here...
I�m so glad... to see you, Annie... Now... I am complete...
Just stay with me, Mom. I�m going to make you well again. Everything�s going to be fine.
You look so handsome. My son... my grown-up son. I�m so proud of you, Annie... so proud... I missed you so much... I love...
"Guiding light" to "old folks home."
...Starships from the Trade Federation and the Commerce Guilds are taking deliveries of battle droids from the foundries on Geonosis.
The droid foundry seems to be working at full capacity. I am going to go down and investigate. I will bring Jango Fett back home for interrogation.
Those Geonosian foundries are part of the Techno Union. We will call in their representatives and ask them a few very pointed questions.
One more thing. Jango mentioned he was recruited by someone named Darth Tyranus. Any idea who that might be?
With the forename Darth, a Sith he must be.
Our missing apprentice. They are playing their hand at last.
Do you believe he could be the mysterious Sido-Dyas, who made the deal for the clone army?
Perhaps too many pieces are missing from this puzzle, there are.
Be careful, Obi-Wan. This investigation is becoming less than routine. Do you need help?
Let me see if I can figure out what's going on first.
Count Dooku must have made a treaty with them.
We must stop them soon before they're fully ready.
Please, please, I don't wish to have emergency powers. That's too extreme a solution. It's akin to a dictatorship. We must rely on the Jedi. Master Yoda, how many are available to go to Geonosis?
Two Hundred,... less or more.
Patience. We should wait for Obi- Wan to report back. We don't know that Count Dooku has made a treaty with the Corporate Alliance, it's speculation.
Out of the question, Senator! You and I are too closely aligned. The issue will become partisan and debates will begin. The proposal must come from a neutral source.
Supreme Chancellor... my august colleagues, I would be proud to propose the motion in question. This is a grave situation, and I'm sure Senator Amidala, and the Queen of Naboo would agree.
If called upon, I will serve. But it will be the saddest day of my life.
(continuing) Thank you.
...Alliance have pledged their armies to Count Dooku and are forming an... Wait!... ah... attack... I don't... make it... aaaggghhh!
I'm going after him!
Yeah, you're right, you're right.
We will deal with Count Dooku. The most important thing for you, Anakin, is to stay where you are. Protect the Senator at all costs. That is your priority.
Understood, Master.
If he's still alive.
...He's like my father, but you heard Master Windu. He gave me strict orders to stay here.

sceneTitle: INT. CORUSCANT, JEDI TEMPLE, COUNCIL CHAMBER - DAY
quote: The longer we wait, the stronger Dooku's armies become. We cannot wait for the Senate to make up its mind about granting the Chancellor emergency powers, in order to be able to use that clone army... We have the authority to go now. We must go now.

sceneTitle: INT. CORUSCANT, JEDI TEMPLE, COUNCIL CHAMBER - DAY
quote: Agreed, Master Windu. Two hundred Jedi send. Enough, let's hope they are.

sceneTitle: INT. CORUSCANT, MAIN SENATE CHAMBER - DAY
quote: In the regrettable absence of Senator Amidala, the chair recognises Senior Representative of Naboo, Jar Jar Binks.

sceneTitle: INT. CORUSCANT, MAIN SENATE CHAMBER - DAY
quote: Senators, dellow felagates...

sceneTitle: INT. CORUSCANT, MAIN SENATE CHAMBER - DAY
quote: In response to the direct threat to the Republic from the Confederacy of Independent Systems, I propose that the Senate gives immediate emergency powers to the Supreme Chancellor.

sceneTitle: INT. CORUSCANT, MAIN SENATE CHAMBER - DAY
quote: (continuing) Who can deny these are exceptional times? Exceptional times demand exceptional measures! Exceptional measures demand exceptional men!

sceneTitle: INT. CORUSCANT, MAIN SENATE CHAMBER - DAY
quote: That is the sentiment every one of us agrees with! And when the shadow of war has dispersed and the bright day of liberty has dawned once again, the power we now give to the Supreme Chancellor will be gladly, and swiftly returned. Out ancient liberties will be restored to us, burnished even more brightly than before!

sceneTitle: INT. CORUSCANT, MAIN SENATE CHAMBER - DAY
quote: It is with great reluctance that I have agreed to this calling. I love democracy... I love the Republic. The fact that this crisis is demanding I be given absolute power to tule over you is evident. But I am mild by nature and have no desire to destroy the democratic process. The power you give me I will lay down when this crisis has abated, I promise you. And all I ask in return is when my current term of office is over, you allow me to reture and live out my life in peace.
Hey, where are you going?
No! You're not!
I'm not letting you go out there. It's too dangerous.
It's my job to protect you. I said it's too dangerous. You're not going, and that's final!
Senator Amidala, I've heard so much about you.
I'm delighted to meet you at last. We have a great deal to discuss, Senator. I hope you can keep your young Jedi under control.
I'll take that weapon.

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, HIGH AUDIENCE CHAMBER - DAY
quote: Get on with it. Carry out the sentence. I want to see her suffer.

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS TUNNEL TO EXECUTION ARENA - DAY
quote: Don't be afraid.

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS TUNNEL TO EXECUTION ARENA - DAY
quote: What are you talking about?

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS TUNNEL TO EXECUTION ARENA - DAY
quote: You love me?! I thought we decided not to fall in love. That we would be forced to live a lie. That it would destroy our lives...

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS TUNNEL TO EXECUTION ARENA - DAY
quote: I have no desire to be cured of this love either. Long or short, I vow to spend the rest of my life with you.
I was beginning to wonder if you had gotten my message.
I retransmitted it as you requested, Master. Then we decided to come and rescue you.
It looks like you're going a good job so far.
I have a bad feeling about this.
Take the one the left. I'll take the one on the right.
What about Padme?
It looks like she's already on top of things.
Foul!! She can't do that... shoot her or something!
You okay?
Jump!!!
This isn't how it's supposed to be! Jango, finish her off.
(smiling enigmatically) Patiece, Viceroy... she will die. Maybe this is the way it's supposed to end.
Master Windu, how pleasant of you to join us. You're just in time for the moment of truth. I would think these two new boys of yours could use a little more training.
Sorry to disappoint you, Dooku. This party's over.
(to Mace Windu) Brave, but stupid, my old Jedi friend. You're impossibly outnumbered.
I don't think so. One Jedi has to be worth a hundred Geonosians.
It wasn't the Geonosians I was thinking about. How well do you think one Jedi will hold up against a thousand battle droids?
Someone's got to - shut down - these droids.
Don't worry! It's being - taken care of!
Master Windu!
(continuing) You have fought gallantly. Worthy of recognition in the history archives of the Jedi Order. Now it is finished. (pauses briefly) Surrender - and your lives will be spared.
We will not be hostages for you to barter with Dooku.
Then, I'm sorry, old friend. You will have to be destroyed.
Come on - hurry! Hurry!
More battalions to the left. Encircle them we must, then divide.
Hold on! Look over there...
It's Dooku, go after him!
(continuing) Padme!!!
(continuing; to pilot) Put the ship down! Down!
No! Forget her. We have to go after Dooku.
No we're not!! Land this ship!
Don't let your personal feelings get in the way. We've got a job to do.
I don't care!.. Go back.
Anakin! She's all right! Look.
(continuing) Follow that speeder!

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: That won't be necessary, Captain. Stand down. And leave them to me.

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: (to Anakin) We move in together - you slowly on the...

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: I'm taking him now!

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: Anakin, no!

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: You'll pay for all the Jedi you've killed today, Dooku.

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: Kenobi, isn't it? As you can see, my Jedi powers are far beyond yours. Now, back down.

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: I don't think so.

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: Ah, but if I must.

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: (continuing) I have spent the last ten years learning to use the power of the Dark Side. It gives me infinitely greater power.

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: You will have to prove it.

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: Grand Master Kenobi, you disappoint me. Yoda holds you in such high esteem.

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: (continuing) Surely you can do better...? (parries) No, I'm surprised. Has Jedi swordsmanship degenerated so quickly, or are you trying to make fun of me? (cuts) Which is it?

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: (continuing) come, come, Master Kenobi. Put me out of my misery.

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: (continuing) That's brave of you, boy - but foolish. I would have thought you'd have learnt your lesson.

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: I'm a slow learner.

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: You have unusual powers, young Padawan. But not enought to save you this time.

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: Don't bet on it!

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: Anakin!

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: Master Yoda. At last we shall know who is the most powerful.

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: Count Dooku. No interest in contests, do I have.

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: (continuing) The end for you, Count, this is.

sceneTitle: INT. GEONOSIS, SECRET HANGER TOWER - LATE DAY
quote: ...Not yet...

sceneTitle: INT. CORUSCANT, SECRET LANDING PLATFORM - DAWN
quote: The Force is with us, my Master.

sceneTitle: INT. CORUSCANT, SECRET LANDING PLATFORM - DAWN
quote: Welcome home, Lord Tyranus. You have done well.

sceneTitle: INT. CORUSCANT, SECRET LANDING PLATFORM - DAWN
quote: I bring you good news, my Lord. The war has begun.

sceneTitle: INT. CORUSCANT, SECRET LANDING PLATFORM - DAWN
quote: Excellent. (smiling) Everything is going as planned.

sceneTitle: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, COUNCIL CHAMBER - SUNSET
quote: Where is your apprentice?

sceneTitle: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, COUNCIL CHAMBER - SUNSET
quote: On his way back to Naboo. He is escorting Senator Amidala home.

sceneTitle: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, COUNCIL CHAMBER - SUNSET
quote: (continuing) I must admit without the clones, it would not have been a victory.

sceneTitle: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, COUNCIL CHAMBER - SUNSET
quote: Victory? Victory, you say?

sceneTitle: INT. JEDI TEMPLE, COUNCIL CHAMBER - SUNSET
quote: (continuing) Not victory, a defeat, it was... Master Obi-Wan. Begun, the Clone War has!

sceneTitle: INT. REBEL BLOCKADE RUNNER - MAIN PASSAGEWAY
quote: Did you hear that? They've shut down the main reactor. We'll be destroyed for sure. This is madness!

sceneTitle: INT. REBEL BLOCKADE RUNNER - MAIN PASSAGEWAY
quote: We're doomed!

sceneTitle: INT. REBEL BLOCKADE RUNNER - MAIN PASSAGEWAY
quote: There'll be no escape for the Princess this time.

sceneTitle: INT. REBEL BLOCKADE RUNNER - MAIN PASSAGEWAY
quote: What's that?
I should have known better than to trust the logic of a half-sized thermocapsulary dehousing assister...
Hurry up! Come with me! What are you waiting for?! Get in gear!
Artoo! Artoo-Detoo, where are you?
At last! Where have you been?
They're heading in this direction. What are we going to do? We'll be sent to the spice mine of Kessel or smashed into who knows what!
Wait a minute, where are you going?
Where are those transmissions you intercepted?
What have you done with those plans?
If this is a consular ship... were is the Ambassador?
Commander, tear this ship apart until you've found those plans and bring me the Ambassador. I want her alive!
Hey, you're not permitted in there. It's restricted. You'll be deactivated for sure..
Don't call me a mindless philosopher, you overweight glob of grease! Now come out before somebody sees you.
Secret mission? What plans? What are you talking about? I'm not getting in there!
I'm going to regret this.
That's funny, the damage doesn't look as bad from out here.
Are you sure this things safe?
Shape it up you guys!... Biggs?
I didn't know you were back! When did you get in?
The Academy didn't change you much...but you're back so soon? Hey, what happened, didn't you get your commission?
I almost forgot. There's a battle going on! Right here in our system. Come and look!

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ANCHORHEAD - SETTLEMENT - POWER STATION -
quote: There they are!

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ANCHORHEAD - SETTLEMENT - POWER STATION -
quote: But there was a lot of firing earlier...

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ANCHORHEAD - SETTLEMENT - POWER STATION -
quote: Hey, easy with those...
Lord Vader, I should have known. Only you could be so bold. The Imperial Senate will not sit for this, when they hear you've attacked a diplomatic...

Don't play games with me, Your Highness. You weren't on any mercy mission this time. You passed directly through a restricted system. Several transmissions were beamed to this ship by Rebel spies. I want to know what happened to the plans they sent you.
I don't know what you're talking about. I'm a member of the Imperial Senate on a diplomatic mission to Alderaan...
You're a part of the Rebel Alliance... and a traitor. Take her away!
I have traced the Rebel spies to her. Now she is my only link to find their secret base!
Leave that to me. Send a distress signal and then inform the senate that all aboard were killed!
She must have hidden the plans in the escape pod. Send a detachment down to retrieve them. See to it personally, Commander. There'll be no one to stop us this time.
How did I get into this mess? I really don't know how. We seem to be made to suffer. It's our lot in life.
I've got to rest before I fall apart. My joints are almost frozen.
What a desolate place this is.
Where are you going?
Well, I'm not going that way. It's much too rocky. This way is much easier.
What makes you think there are settlements over there?
Don't get technical with me.
What mission? What are you talking about? I've had just about enough of you! Go that way! You'll be malfunctioning within a day, you nearsighted scrap pile!
And don't let me catch you following me begging for help, because you won't get it.
No more adventures. I'm not going that way.
That malfunctioning little twerp. This is all his fault! He tricked me into going this way, but he'll do no better.
Wait, what's that? A transport! I'm saved!
Over here! Help! Please, help!

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ANCHORHEAD SETTLEMENT - POWER STATION - DAY
quote: (Very animated) ...so I cut off my power, shut down the afterburners and came in low on Deak's trail. I was so close I thought I was going to fry my instruments. As it was I busted up the Skyhopper pretty bad. Uncle Owen was pretty upset. He grounded me for the rest of the season. You should have been there... it was fantastic.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ANCHORHEAD SETTLEMENT - POWER STATION - DAY
quote: Look who's talking. Now that you've been around those giant starships you're beginning to sound like my uncle. You've gotten soft in the city...

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ANCHORHEAD SETTLEMENT - POWER STATION - DAY
quote: Well, things haven't been the same since you left, Biggs. It's been so... quiet.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ANCHORHEAD SETTLEMENT - POWER STATION - DAY
quote: What are you talking about?

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ANCHORHEAD SETTLEMENT - POWER STATION - DAY
quote: Join the Rebellion?! Are you kidding! How?

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ANCHORHEAD SETTLEMENT - POWER STATION - DAY
quote: I'm sorry. I'm quiet. (he whispers) Listen how quiet I am. You can barely hear me...

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ANCHORHEAD SETTLEMENT - POWER STATION - DAY
quote: You're crazy! You could wander around forever trying to find them.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ANCHORHEAD SETTLEMENT - POWER STATION - DAY
quote: And I'm stuck here...

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ANCHORHEAD SETTLEMENT - POWER STATION - DAY
quote: Not likely! I had to cancel my application. There has been a lot of unrest among the Sandpeople since you left... they've even raided the outskirts of Anchorhead.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ANCHORHEAD SETTLEMENT - POWER STATION - DAY
quote: I know, but he's got enough vaporators going to make the place pay off. He needs me for just one more season. I can't leave him now.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ANCHORHEAD SETTLEMENT - POWER STATION - DAY
quote: It couldn't happen here. You said it yourself. The Empire won't bother with this rock.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ANCHORHEAD SETTLEMENT - POWER STATION - DAY
quote: I wish I was going... Are you going to be around long?

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ANCHORHEAD SETTLEMENT - POWER STATION - DAY
quote: Then I guess I won't see you.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ANCHORHEAD SETTLEMENT - POWER STATION - DAY
quote: Well, I'll be at the Academy next season... after that who knows. I won't be drafted into the Imperial Starfleet that's for sure... Take care of yourself, you'll always be the best friend I've got.
Artoo-Detoo! It's you! It's you!
Wake up! Wake up!
We're doomed.
Do you think they'll melt us down?
Don't shoot! Don't shoot! Will this never end?

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - DESERT - LARS HOMESTEAD - AFTERNOON
quote: It looks like we don't have much of a choice but I'll remind him.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - DESERT - LARS HOMESTEAD - AFTERNOON
quote: (quickly) Sir -- not in an environment such as this -- that's why I've also been programmed for over thirty secondary functions that...

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - DESERT - LARS HOMESTEAD - AFTERNOON
quote: Vaporators! Sir -- My first job was programming binary load lifter... very similar to your vaporators. You could say...

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - DESERT - LARS HOMESTEAD - AFTERNOON
quote: Of course I can, sir. It's like a second language for me... I'm as fluent in Bocce...

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - DESERT - LARS HOMESTEAD - AFTERNOON
quote: Shutting up, sir.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - DESERT - LARS HOMESTEAD - AFTERNOON
quote: But I was going into Toshi Station to pick up some power converters...

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - DESERT - LARS HOMESTEAD - AFTERNOON
quote: All right, come on! And the red one, come on. Well, come on, Red, let's go.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - DESERT - LARS HOMESTEAD - AFTERNOON
quote: Uncle Owen...

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - DESERT - LARS HOMESTEAD - AFTERNOON
quote: This R2 unit has a bad motivator. Look!

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - DESERT - LARS HOMESTEAD - AFTERNOON
quote: (pointing to Artoo) Excuse me, sir, but that R2 unit is in prime condition. A real bargain.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - DESERT - LARS HOMESTEAD - AFTERNOON
quote: Uncle Owen...

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - DESERT - LARS HOMESTEAD - AFTERNOON
quote: What about that one?

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - DESERT - LARS HOMESTEAD - AFTERNOON
quote: Yeah, take it away.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - DESERT - LARS HOMESTEAD - AFTERNOON
quote: Uh, I'm quite sure you'll be very pleased with that one, sir. He really is in first-class condition. I've worked with him before. Here he comes.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - DESERT - LARS HOMESTEAD - AFTERNOON
quote: Okay, let's go.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - DESERT - LARS HOMESTEAD - AFTERNOON
quote: (to Artoo) Now, don't you forget this! Why I should stick my neck out for you is quite beyond my capacity!

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Thank the maker! This oil bath is going to feel so good. I've got such a bad case of dust contamination, I can barely move!

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: It just isn't fair. Oh, Biggs is right. I'm never gonna get out of here!

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Is there anything I might do to help?

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Well, not unless you can alter time, speed up the harvest, or teleport me off this rock!

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: I don't think so, sir. I'm only a droid and not very knowledgeable about such things. Not on this planet, anyways. As a matter of fact, I'm not even sure which planet I'm on.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Well, if there's a bright center to the universe, you're on the planet that it's farthest from.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: I see, sir.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Uh, you can call me Luke.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: I see, sir Luke.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: (laughing) Just Luke.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: And I am See-Threepio, human-cyborg relations, and this is my counterpart, Artoo-Detoo.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Hello.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: You got a lot of carbon scoring here. It looks like you boys have seen a lot of action.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: With all we've been through, sometimes I'm amazed we're in as good condition as we are, what with the Rebellion and all.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: You know of the Rebellion against the Empire?

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: That's how we came to be in your service, if you take my meaning, sir.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Have you been in many battles?

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Several, I think. Actually, there's not much to tell. I'm not much more than an interpreter, and not very good at telling stories. Well, not at making them interesting, anyways.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Well, my little friend, you've got something jammed in here real good. Were you on a cruiser or...

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Help me, Obi-Wan Kenobi. You're my only hope.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: What's this?

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: What is what?!? He asked you a question... (pointing to Leia) What is that?

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Help me, Obi-Wan Kenobi. You're my only hope. Help me, Obi-Wan Kenobi. You're my only hope.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Oh, he says it's nothing, sir. Merely a malfunction. Old data. Pay it no mind.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Who is she? She's beautiful.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: I'm afraid I'm not quite sure, sir.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Help me, Obi-Wan Kenobi...

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: I think she was a passenger on our last voyage. A person of some importance, sir -- I believe. Our captain was attached to...

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Is there more to this recording?

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Behave yourself, Artoo. You're going to get us in trouble. It's all right, you can trust him. He's our new master.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: He says he's the property of Obi-Wan Kenobi, a resident of these parts. And it's a private message for him. Quite frankly, sir I don't know what he's talking about. Our last master was Captain Antilles, but with what we've been through, this little R2 unit has become a bit eccentric.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Obi-Wan Kenobi? I wonder if he means old Ben Kenobi?

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: I beg your pardon, sir, but do you know what he's talking about?

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Well, I don't know anyone named Obi- Wan, but old Ben lives out beyond the dune sea. He's kind of a strange old hermit.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: I wonder who she is. It sounds like she's in trouble. I'd better play back the whole thing.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: He says the restraining bolt has short circuited his recording system. He suggests that if you remove the bolt, he might be able to play back the entire recording.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: H'm? Oh, yeah, well, I guess you're too small to run away on me if I take this off! Okay.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: There you go.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Well, wait a minute. Where'd she go? Bring her back! Play back the entire message.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: What message? The one you're carrying inside your rusty innards!

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: All right, I'll be right there, Aunt Beru.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: I'm sorry, sir, but he appears to have picked up a slight flutter.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: Well, see what you can do with him. I'll be right back.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: (to Artoo) Just you reconsider playing that message for him.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: No, I don't think he likes you at all.

sceneTitle: INT. LARS HOMESTEAD - GARAGE AREA - LATE AFTERNOON
quote: No, I don't like you either.
You know, I think that R2 unit we bought might have been stolen.
Well, I stumbled across a recording while I was cleaning him. He says he belongs to someone called Obi-Wan Kenobi.
I thought he might have meant old Ben. Do you know what he's talking about? Well, I wonder if he's related to Ben.
But what if this Obi-Wan comes looking for him?
He knew my father?

Yes, sir. I think those new droids are going to work out fine. In fact, I, uh, was also thinking about our agreement about my staying on another season. And if these new droids do work out, I want to transmit my application to the Academy this year.
Sure, there're more than enough droids.
But it's a whole 'nother year.
Yeah, that's what you said last year when Biggs and Tank left.
It looks like I'm going nowhere. I have to finish cleaning those droids.
What are you doing hiding there?
It wasn't my fault, sir. Please don't deactivate me. I told him not to go, but he's faulty, malfunctioning; kept babbling on about his mission.
Oh, no!
That R2 unit has always been a problem. These astro-droids are getting quite out of hand. Even I can't understand their logic at times.
How could I be so stupid? He's nowhere in sight. Blast it!
Pardon me, sir, but couldn't we go after him?
It's too dangerous with all the Sandpeople around. We'll have to wait until morning.
All right, I'll be there in a few minutes. Boy, am I gonna get it.
You know that little droid is going to cause me a lot of trouble.
Oh, he excels at that, sir.

sceneTitle: INT./EXT. LUKE'S SPEEDER - DESERT WASTELAND - TRAVELING -
quote: (yelling) How's that.

sceneTitle: INT./EXT. LUKE'S SPEEDER - DESERT WASTELAND - TRAVELING -
quote: Old Ben Kenobi lives out in this direction somewhere, but I don't see how that R2 unit could have come this far. We must have missed him. Uncle Owen isn't going to take this very well.

sceneTitle: INT./EXT. LUKE'S SPEEDER - DESERT WASTELAND - TRAVELING -
quote: Sir, would it help if you told him it was my fault.

sceneTitle: INT./EXT. LUKE'S SPEEDER - DESERT WASTELAND - TRAVELING -
quote: (brightening) Sure. He needs you. He'd probably only deactivate you for a day or so...

sceneTitle: INT./EXT. LUKE'S SPEEDER - DESERT WASTELAND - TRAVELING -
quote: Deactivate! Well, on the other hand if you hadn't removed his restraining bolt...

sceneTitle: INT./EXT. LUKE'S SPEEDER - DESERT WASTELAND - TRAVELING -
quote: Wait, there's something dead ahead on the scanner. It looks like our droid... hit the accelerator.
Hey, whoa, just where do you think you're going?

Master Luke here is your rightful owner. We'll have no more of this Obi-Wan Kenobi jibberish... and don't talk to me about your mission, either. You're fortunate he doesn't blast you into a million pieces right here.
Well, come on. It's getting late. I only hope we can get back before Uncle Owen really blows up.
If you don't mind my saying so, sir, I think you should deactivate the little fugitive until you've gotten him back to your workshop.
No, he's not going to try anything.
What's wrong with him now?
Oh my... sir, he says there are several creatures approaching from the southeast.
Sandpeople! Or worst! Come on, let's have a look. Come on.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ROCK CANYON - RIDGE - DAY
quote: There are two Banthas down there but I don't see any... wait a second, they're Sandpeople all right. I can see one of them now.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ROCK CANYON - FLOOR - DAY
quote: Hello there! Come here my little friend. Don't be afraid.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ROCK CANYON - FLOOR - DAY
quote: Don't worry, he'll be all right.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ROCK CANYON - FLOOR - DAY
quote: What happened?

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ROCK CANYON - FLOOR - DAY
quote: Rest easy, son, you've had a busy day. You're fortunate you're still in one piece.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ROCK CANYON - FLOOR - DAY
quote: Ben? Ben Kenobi! Boy, am I glad to see you!

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ROCK CANYON - FLOOR - DAY
quote: The Jundland wastes are not to be traveled lightly. Tell me young Luke, what brings you out this far?

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ROCK CANYON - FLOOR - DAY
quote: Oh, this little droid! I think he's searching for his former master... I've never seen such devotion in a droid before... there seems to be no stopping him. He claims to be the property of an Obi-Wan Kenobi. Is he a relative of yours? Do you know who he's talking about?

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ROCK CANYON - FLOOR - DAY
quote: Obi-Wan Kenobi... Obi-Wan? Now thats a name I haven't heard in a long time... a long time.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ROCK CANYON - FLOOR - DAY
quote: I think my uncle knew him. He said he was dead.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ROCK CANYON - FLOOR - DAY
quote: Oh, he's not dead, not... not yet.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ROCK CANYON - FLOOR - DAY
quote: You know him!

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ROCK CANYON - FLOOR - DAY
quote: Well of course, of course I know him. He's me! I haven't gone by the name Obi-Wan since oh, before you were born.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ROCK CANYON - FLOOR - DAY
quote: Then the droid does belong to you.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ROCK CANYON - FLOOR - DAY
quote: Don't seem to remember ever owning a droid. Very interesting...

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ROCK CANYON - FLOOR - DAY
quote: I think we better get indoors. The Sandpeople are easily startled but they will soon be back and in greater numbers.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - ROCK CANYON - FLOOR - DAY
quote: Threepio!

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - SAND PIT - ROCK MESA - DAY
quote: Where am I? I must have taken a bad step...

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - SAND PIT - ROCK MESA - DAY
quote: Can you stand? We've got to get out of here before the Sandpeople return.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - SAND PIT - ROCK MESA - DAY
quote: I don't think I can make it. You go on, Master Luke. There's no sense in you risking yourself on my account. I'm done for.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - SAND PIT - ROCK MESA - DAY
quote: No, you're not. What kind of talk is that?

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - SAND PIT - ROCK MESA - DAY
quote: Quickly, son... they're on the move.
No, my father didn't fight in the wars. He was a navigator on a spice freighter.
That's what your uncle told you. He didn't hold with your father's ideals. Thought he should have stayed here and not gotten involved.
You fought in the Clone Wars?
Yes, I was once a Jedi Knight the same as your father.
I wish I'd known him.
He was the best star-pilot in the galaxy, and a cunning warrior. I understand you've become quite a good pilot yourself. And he was a good friend. Which reminds me...

I have something here for you. Your father wanted you to have this when you were old enough, but your uncle wouldn't allow it. He feared you might follow old Obi-Wan on some damned-fool idealistic crusade like your father did.
Sir, if you'll not be needing me, I'll close down for awhile.
Sure, go ahead.
What is it?
Your fathers lightsaber. This is the weapon of a Jedi Knight. Not as clumsy or as random as a blaster.
An elegant weapon for a more civilized time. For over a thousand generations the Jedi Knights were the guardians of peace and justice in the Old Republic. Before the dark times, before the Empire.
How did my father die?

A young Jedi named Darth Vader, who was a pupil of mine until he turned to evil, helped the Empire hunt down and destroy the Jedi Knights. He betrayed and murdered your father. Now the Jedi are all but extinct. Vader was seduced by the dark side of the Force.
The Force?
Well, the Force is what gives a Jedi his power. It's an energy field created by all living things. It surrounds us and penetrates us. It binds the galaxy together.
Now, let's see if we can't figure out what you are, my little friend. And where you come from.
I saw part of the message he was...
I seem to have found it.

General Kenobi, years ago you served my father in the Clone Wars. Now he begs you to help him in his struggle against the Empire. I regret that I am unable to present my father's request to you in person, but my ship has fallen under attack and I'm afraid my mission to bring you to Alderaan has failed. I have placed information vital to the survival of the Rebellion into the memory systems of this R2 unit. My father will know how to retrieve it. You must see this droid safely delivered to him on Alderaan. This is our most desperate hour. Help me, Obi-Wan Kenobi, you're my only hope.
You must learn the ways of the Force if you're to come with me to Alderaan.
(laughing) Alderaan? I'm not going to Alderaan. I've got to go home. It's late, I'm in for it as it is.
I need your help, Luke. She needs your help. I'm getting too old for this sort of thing.
I can't get involved! I've got work to do! It's not that I like the Empire. I hate it! But there's nothing I can do about it right now. It's such a long way from here.
That's your uncle talking.
(sighing) Oh, God, my uncle. How am I ever going to explain this?
Learn about the Force, Luke.
Look, I can take you as far as Anchorhead. You can get a transport there to Mos Eisley or wherever you're going.
You must do what you feel is right, of course.
The Imperial Senate will no longer be of any concern to us. I've just received word that the Emperor has dissolved the council permanently. The last remnants of the Old Republic have been swept away.
The regional governors now have direct control over territories. Fear will keep the local systems in line. Fear of this battle station.
The plans you refer to will soon be back in our hands.
Don't be too proud of this technological terror you've constructed. The ability to destroy a planet is insignificant next to the power of the Force.
I find your lack of faith disturbing.
Enough of this! Vader, release him!
As you wish.
This bickering is pointless. Lord Vader will provide us with the location of the Rebel fortress by the time this station is operational. We will then crush the Rebellion with one swift stroke.
It looks like Sandpeople did this, all right. Look, here are Gaffi sticks, Bantha tracks. It's just... I never heard of them hitting anything this big before.
They didn't. But we are meant to think they did. These tracks are side by side. Sandpeople always ride single file to hide there numbers.
These are the same Jawas that sold us Artoo and Threepio.
And these blast points, too accurate for Sandpeople. Only Imperial stormtroopers are so precise.
Why would Imperial troops want to slaughter Jawas?
If they traced the robots here, they may have learned who they sold them to. And that would lead them home!
Wait, Luke! It's too dangerous.
Uncle Owen! Aunt Beru! Uncle Owen!
And, now Your Highness, we will discuss the location of your hidden Rebel base.
There's nothing you could have done, Luke, had you been there. You'd have been killed, too, and the droids would be in the hands of the Empire.
I want to come with you to Alderaan. There's nothing here for me now. I want to learn the ways of the Force and become a Jedi like my father.
Mos Eisley Spaceport. You will never find a more wretched hive of scum and villainy. We must be cautious.
About three or four seasons.
They're for sale if you want them.
You don't need to see his identification.
These are not the droids your looking for.
He can go about his business.
(to Luke) Move along.
I can't abide these Jawas. Disgusting creatures.
Go on, go on. I can't understand how we got by those troopers. I thought we were dead.
The Force can have a strong influence on the weak-minded. You will find it a powerful ally.
Do you really think we're going to find a pilot here that'll take us to Alderaan?
Well, most of the best freighter pilots can be found here. Only watch your step. This place can be a little rough.
I'm ready for anything.
Come along, Artoo.
What?
Listen, why don't you wait out by the speeder. We don't want any trouble.
I heartily agree with you sir.
I'm sorry.
I'll be careful than.
This little one isn't worth the effort. Come let me buy you something...
This is Chewbacca. He's first-mate on a ship that might suit our needs.
I don't like the look of this.
Han Solo. I'm captain of the Millennium Falcon. Chewie here tells me you're looking for passage to the Alderaan system.
Yes, indeed. If it's a fast ship.
Fast ship? You've never heard of the Millennium Falcon?
Should I have?
It's the ship that made the Kessel run in less than twelve parsecs!
I've outrun Imperial starships, not the local bulk-cruisers, mind you. I'm talking about the big Corellian ships now. She's fast enough for you, old man. What's the cargo?
Only passengers. Myself, the boy, two droids, and no questions asked.
What is it? Some kind of local trouble?
Let's just say we'd like to avoid any Imperial entanglements.
Well, that's the trick, isn't it? And it's going to cost you something extra. Ten thousand in advance.
Ten thousand? We could almost buy our own ship for that!
But who's going to fly it, kid! You?
You bet I could. I'm not such a bad pilot myself! We don't have to sit here and listen...
We haven't that much with us. But we could pay you two thousand now, plus fifteen when we reach Alderaan.
Seventeen, huh!
Okay. You guys got yourself a ship. We'll leave as soon as you're ready. Docking bay Ninety-four.
Ninety-four.
Looks like somebody's beginning to take an interest in your handiwork.
Seventeen thousand! Those guys must really be desperate. This could really save my neck. Get back to the ship and get her ready.
You'll have to sell your speeder.
That's okay. I'm never coming back to this planet again.
Yes, Greedo. As a matter of fact, I was just going to see your boss. Tell Jabba that I've got his money.
Yeah, but this time I got the money.
I don't have it with me. Tell Jabba...
Even I get boarded sometimes. Do you think I had a choice?
Over my dead body.
Yes, I'll bet you have.
Sorry about the mess.
Her resistance to the mind probe is considerable. It will be some time before we can extract any information from her.
Perhaps she would respond to an alternative form of persuasion.
What do you mean?
I think it is time we demonstrate the full power of this station. (to soldier) Set your course for Princess Leia's home planet of Alderaan.
Lock the door, Artoo.
I would much rather have gone with Master Luke than stay here with you. I don't know what all the trouble is about, but I'm sure it must be your fault.
You watch your language!

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - MOS EISLEY - STREET - ALLEYWAY - USED
quote: He says it's the best he can do. Since the XP-38 came out, they're just not in demand.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - MOS EISLEY - STREET - ALLEYWAY - USED
quote: It will be enough.

sceneTitle: EXT. TATOOINE - MOS EISLEY - STREET - ALLEYWAY - USED
quote: If the ship's as fast as he's boasting, we ought to do well.
Come on out, Solo!
I've been waiting for you, Jabba.
I expected you would be.
I'm not the type to run.
(fatherly-smooth) Han, my boy, there are times when you disappoint me... why haven't you paid me? And why did you have to fry poor Greedo like that... after all we've been through together.
You sent Greedo to blast me.
(mock surprise) Han, why you're the best smuggler in the business. You're too valuable to fry. He was only relaying my concern at your delays. He wasn't going to blast you.
I think he thought he was. Next time don't send one of those twerps. If you've got something to say to me, come see me yourself.

Han, Han! If only you hadn't had to dump that shipment of spice... you understand I just can't make an exception. Where would I be if every pilot who smuggled for me dumped their shipment at the first sign of an Imperial starship? It's not good business.
You know, even I get boarded sometimes, Jabba. I had no choice, but I've got a charter now and I can pay you back, plus a little extra. I just need some more time.

(to his men) Put your blasters away. Han, my boy, I'm only doing this because you're the best and I need you. So, for an extra, say twenty percent I'll give you a little more time... but this is it. If you disappoint me again, I'll put a price on your head so large you won't be able to go near a civilized system for the rest of your short life.
Jabba, I'll pay you because it's my pleasure.

sceneTitle: INT. MOS EISLEY SPACEPORT - DOCKING BAY 94
quote: What a piece of junk.

sceneTitle: INT. MOS EISLEY SPACEPORT - DOCKING BAY 94
quote: She'll make point five beyond the speed of light. She may not look like much, but she's got it where it counts, kid. I've added some special modifications myself.

sceneTitle: INT. MOS EISLEY SPACEPORT - DOCKING BAY 94
quote: We're a little rushed, so if you'll hurry aboard we'll get out of here.

sceneTitle: INT. MOS EISLEY SPACEPORT - DOCKING BAY 94
quote: Hello, sir.
Chewie, get us out of here!
Oh, my. I'd forgotten how much I hate space travel.
It looks like an Imperial cruiser. Our passengers must be hotter than I thought. Try and hold them off. Angle the deflector shield while I make the calculations for the jump to light speed.
Stay sharp! There are two more coming in; they're going to try to cut us off.
Why don't you outrun them? I thought you said this thing was fast.
Watch your mouth, kid, or you're going to find yourself floating home. We'll be safe enough once we make the jump to hyperspace. Besides, I know a few maneuvers. We'll lose them!
Here's where the fun begins!
How long before you can make the jump to light speed?
It'll take a few moments to get the coordinates from the navi-computer.
Are you kidding? At the rate they're gaining...

Traveling through hyperspace isn't like dusting crops, boy! Without precise calculations we could fly right through a star or bounce too close to a supernova and that'd end your trip real quick, wouldn't it?
What's that flashing?
We're losing our deflector shield. Go strap yourself in, I'm going to make the jump to light speed.
Governor Tarkin, I should have expected to find you holding Vader's leash. I recognized your foul stench when I was brought on board.
Charming to the last. You don't know how hard I found it signing the order to terminate your life!
I surprised you had the courage to take the responsibility yourself!
Princess Leia, before your execution I would like you to be my guest at a ceremony that will make this battle station operational. No star system will dare oppose the Emperor now.
The more you tighten your grip, Tarkin, the more star systems will slip through your fingers.

Not after we demonstrate the power of this station. In a way, you have determined the choice of the planet that'll be destroyed first. Since you are reluctant to provide us with the location of the Rebel base, I have chosen to test this station's destructive power... on your home planet of Alderaan.
No! Alderaan is peaceful. We have no weapons. You can't possibly...
You would prefer another target? A military target? Then name the system!
I grow tired of asking this. So it'll be the last time. Where is the Rebel base?
(softly) Dantooine.
They're on Dantooine.
There. You see Lord Vader, she can be reasonable. (addressing Motti) Continue with the operation. You may fire when ready.
What?
You're far too trusting. Dantooine is too remote to make an effective demonstration. But don't worry. We will deal with your Rebel friends soon enough.
No!
Commence primary ignition.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: Are you all right? What's wrong?

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: I felt a great disturbance in the Force... as if millions of voices suddenly cried out in terror and were suddenly silenced. I fear something terrible has happened.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: You'd better get on with your exercises.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: Well, you can forget your troubles with those Imperial slugs. I told you I'd outrun 'em.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: Don't everyone thank me at once.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: Anyway, we should be at Alderaan about oh-two-hundred hours.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: Now be careful, Artoo.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: He made a fair move. Screaming about it won't help you.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: (interrupting) Let him have it. It's not wise to upset a Wookiee.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: But sir, nobody worries about upsetting a droid.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: That's 'cause droids don't pull people's arms out of their socket when they lose. Wookiees are known to do that.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: I see your point, sir. I suggest a new strategy, Artoo. Let the Wookiee win.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: Remember, a Jedi can feel the Force flowing through him.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: You mean it controls your actions?

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: Partially. But it also obeys your commands.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: Hokey religions and ancient weapons are no match for a good blaster at your side, kid.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: You don't believe in the Force, do you?

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: Kid, I've flown from one side of this galaxy to the other. I've seen a lot of strange stuff, but I've never seen anything to make me believe there's one all-powerful force controlling everything. There's no mystical energy field that controls my destiny.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: It's all a lot of simple tricks and nonsense.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: I suggest you try it again, Luke.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: This time, let go your conscious self and act on instinct.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: (laughing) With the blast shield down, I can't even see. How am I supposed to fight?

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: Your eyes can deceive you. Don't trust them.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: Stretch out with your feelings.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: You see, you can do it.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: I call it luck.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: In my experience, there's no such thing as luck.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: Look, going good against remotes is one thing. Going good against the living? That's something else.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: Looks like we're coming up on Alderaan.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: You know, I did feel something. I could almost see the remote.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: That's good. You have taken your first step into a larger world.
Yes.
She lied! She lied to us!
I told you she would never consciously betray the Rebellion.
Terminate her... immediately!
Stand by, Chewie, here we go. Cut in the sublight engines.
What the...? Aw, we've come out of hyperspace into a meteor shower. Some kind of asteroid collision. It's not on any of the charts.
What's going on?
Our position is correct, except... no, Alderaan!
What do you mean? Where is it?
Thats what I'm trying to tell you, kid. It ain't there. It's been totally blown away.
What? How?
Destroyed... by the Empire!
The entire starfleet couldn't destroy the whole planet. It'd take a thousand ships with more fire power than I've...
There's another ship coming in.
Maybe they know what happened.
It's an Imperial fighter.
It followed us!
No. It's a short range fighter.
There aren't any bases around here. Where did it come from?
It sure is leaving in a big hurry. If they identify us, we're in big trouble.
Not if I can help it. Chewie...jam it's transmissions.
It'd be as well to let it go. It's too far out of range.
Not for long...
A fighter that size couldn't get this deep into space on its own.
It must have gotten lost, been part of a convoy or something.
Well, he ain't going to be around long enough to tell anyone about us.
Look at him. He's headed for that small moon.
I think I can get him before he gets there... he's almost in range.
That's no moon! It's a space station.
It's too big to be a space station.
I have a very bad feeling about this.
Yeah, I think your right. Full reverse! Chewie, lock in the auxiliary power.
Why are we still moving towards it?
We're caught in a tractor beam! It's pulling us in!
But there's gotta be something you can do!
There's nothin' I can do about it, kid. I'm in full power. I'm going to have to shut down. But they're not going to get me without a fight!
You can't win. But there are alternatives to fighting.
Yes.
They must be trying to return the stolen plans to the princess. She may yet be of some use to us.
Did you find any droids?
Send a scanning crew on board. I want every part of this ship checked.
I sense something... a presence I haven't felt since...
Boy, it's lucky you had these compartments.
I use them for smuggling. I never thought I'd be smuggling myself in them. This is ridiculous. Even if I could take off, I'd never get past the tractor beam.
Leave that to me!
Damn fool. I knew that you were going to say that!
Who's the more foolish... the fool or the fool who follows him?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: You know, between his howling and your blasting everything in sight, it's a wonder the whole station doesn't know we're here.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Bring them on! I prefer a straight fight to all this sneaking around.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: We found the computer outlet, sir.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Plug in. He should be able to interpret the entire Imperial computer network.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: He says he's found the main computer to power the tractor beam that's holding the ship here. He'll try to make the precise location appear on the monitor.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: The tractor beam is coupled to the main reactor in seven locations. A power loss at one of the terminals will allow the ship to leave.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: I don't think you boys can help. I must go alone.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Whatever you say. I've done more that I bargained for on this trip already.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: I want to go with you.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Be patient, Luke. Stay and watch over the droids.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: But he can...

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: They must be delivered safely or other star systems will suffer the same fate as Alderaan. Your destiny lies along a different path than mine. The Force will be with you... always!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Boy you said it, Chewie.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Where did you dig up that old fossil?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Ben is a great man.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Yeah, great at getting us into trouble.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: I didn't hear you give any ideas...

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Well, anything would be better than just hanging around waiting for him to pick us up...

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Who do you think...

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: What is it?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: I'm afraid I'm not quite sure, sir. He says "I found her", and keeps repeating, "She's here."

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Well, who... who has he found?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Princess Leia.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: The princess? She's here?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Princess? What's going on?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Level five. Detention block A A-twenty- three. I'm afraid she's scheduled to be terminated.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Oh, no! We've got to do something.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: What are you talking about?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: The droid belongs to her. She's the one in the message... We've got to help her.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Now, look, don't get any funny ideas. The old man wants us to wait right here.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: But he didn't know she was here. Look, will you just find a way back into the detention block?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: I'm not going anywhere.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: They're going to execute her. Look, a few minutes ago you said you didn't want to just wait here to be captured. Now all you want to do is stay.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Marching into the detention area is not what I had in mind.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: But they're going to kill her!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Better her than me...

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: She's rich.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Rich?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Yes. Rich, powerful! Listen, if you were to rescue her, the reward would be...

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: What?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Well more wealth that you can imagine.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: I don't know, I can imagine quite a bit!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: You'll get it!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: I better!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: You will...

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: All right, kid. But you'd better be right about this.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: All right.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: What's your plan?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Uh... Threepio, hand me those binders there will you?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Okay. Now, I'm going to put these on you.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Okay. Han, you put these on.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Don't worry, Chewie. I think I know what he has in mind.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Master Luke, sir! Pardon me for asking... but, ah... what should Artoo and I do if we're discovered here?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Lock the door!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: And hope they don't have blasters.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - FORWARD BAY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: That isn't very reassuring.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - DETENTION AREA - ELEVATOR TUBE
quote: I can't see a thing in this helmet.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - INTERIOR ELEVATOR - DETENTION SECURITY
quote: This is not going to work.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - INTERIOR ELEVATOR - DETENTION SECURITY
quote: Why didn't you say so before?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - INTERIOR ELEVATOR - DETENTION SECURITY
quote: I did say so before!
Prisoner transfer from Block one-one- three-eight.
Look out! He's loose!
He's going to pull us all apart.
Go get him!
We've got to find out which cell this princess of yours is in. Here it is... cell twenty-one-eight-seven. You go get her. I'll hold them here.
(sounding official) Everything is under control. Situation normal.
(getting nervous) Uh... had a slight weapons malfunction. But, uh, everything's perfectly all right now. We're fine. We're all fine here, now, thank you. How are you?
Uh, uh, negative. We had a reactor leak here now. Give us a few minutes to lock it down. Large leak... very dangerous.
Boring conversation anyway. (yelling down the hall) Luke! We're going to have company!
(finally) Aren't you a little short to be a stormtrooper?
What? Oh... the uniform. I'm Luke Skywalker. I'm here to rescue you.
You're who?
I'm here to rescue you. I've got your R2 unit. I'm here with Ben Kenobi.
Ben Kenobi is here! Where is he?
Come on!
He is here...
Obi-Wan Kenobi! What makes you think so?
A tremor in the Force. The last time I felt it was in the presence of my old master.
Surely he must be dead by now.
Don't underestimate the power of the Force.
The Jedi are extinct, their fire has gone out of the universe. You, my friend, are all that's left of their religion.
Yes.
The princess! Put all sections on alert!
Obi-Wan is here. The Force is with him.
If you're right, he must not be allowed to escape.
Escape is not his plan. I must face him alone.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - DETENTION AREA - HALLWAY
quote: Chewie!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - DETENTION AREA - HALLWAY
quote: Get behind me! Get behind me!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - DETENTION AREA - HALLWAY
quote: Can't get out that way.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - DETENTION AREA - HALLWAY
quote: Looks like you managed to cut off our only escape route.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - DETENTION AREA - HALLWAY
quote: (sarcastically) Maybe you'd like it back in your cell, Your Highness.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - DETENTION AREA - HALLWAY
quote: See-Threepio! See-Threepio!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - DETENTION AREA - HALLWAY
quote: (over comlink) Yes sir?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - DETENTION AREA - HALLWAY
quote: We've been cut off! Are there any other ways out of the cell bay?... What was that? I didn't copy!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN BAY GANTRY - CONTROL TOWER
quote: I said, all systems have been alerted to your presence, sir. The main entrance seems to be the only way in or out; all other information on your level is restricted.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN BAY GANTRY - CONTROL TOWER
quote: Oh, no!
There isn't any other way out.
I can't hold them off forever! Now what?
This is some rescue. When you came in here, didn't you have a plan for getting out?
(pointing to Luke) He's the brains, sweetheart.
Well, I didn't...
What the hell are you doing?
Somebody has to save our skins. Into the garbage chute, wise guy.
Get in there you big furry oaf! I don't care what you smell! Get in there and don't worry about it.
Wonderful girl! Either I'm going to kill her or I'm beginning to like her. Get in there!
(sarcastically) Oh! The garbage chute was a really wonderful idea. What an incredible smell you've discovered! Let's get out of here! Get away from there...
No! wait!
Will you forget it? I already tried it. It's magnetically sealed!
Put that thing away! You're going to get us all killed.
Absolutely, Your Worship. Look, I had everything under control until you led us down here. You know, it's not going to take them long to figure out what happened to us.
It could be worse...
It's worse.
There's something alive in here!
That's your imagination.
Something just moves past my leg! Look! Did you see that?
What?
Help!
Luke! Luke! Luke!
Luke!
Luke, Luke, grab a hold of this.
Blast it, will you! My gun's jammed.
Where?
Anywhere! Oh!!
Luke! Luke!
Grab him!
What happened?
I don't know, it just let go of me and disappeared...
I've got a very bad feeling about this.
The walls are moving!
Don't just stand there. Try to brace it with something.
Wait a minute!
Threepio! Come in Threepio! Threepio! Where could he be?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN GANTRY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: They're madmen! They're heading for the prison level. If you hurry, you might catch them.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN GANTRY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: (to Artoo) Come on!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN GANTRY - COMMAND OFFICE
quote: Oh! All this excitement has overrun the circuits of my counterpart here. If you don't mind, I'd like to take him down to maintenance.
Threepio! Come in, Threepio! Threepio!
Get to the top!
I can't
Where could he be? Threepio! Threepio, will you come in?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN FORWARD BAY - SERVICE PANEL
quote: They aren't here! Something must have happened to them. See if they've been captured.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN FORWARD BAY - SERVICE PANEL
quote: Hurry!
One thing's for sure. We're all going to be a lot thinner! (to Leia) Get on top of it!
I'm trying!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN FORWARD BAY - SERVICE PANEL
quote: (to Artoo) Thank goodness, they haven't found them! Where could they be?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN FORWARD BAY - SERVICE PANEL
quote: Use the comlink? Oh, my! I forgot I turned it off!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN FORWARD BAY - SERVICE PANEL
quote: Are you there, sir?
Threepio!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN FORWARD BAY - SERVICE PANEL
quote: We've had some problems...

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN FORWARD BAY - SERVICE PANEL
quote: (over comlink) Will you shut up and listen to me? Shut down all garbage mashers on the detention level, will you? Do you copy?
Shut down all the garbage mashers on the detention level.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN FORWARD BAY - SERVICE PANEL
quote: (over comlink) Shut down all the garbage mashers on the detention level.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN FORWARD BAY - SERVICE PANEL
quote: (to Artoo) No. Shut them all down! Hurry!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN FORWARD BAY - SERVICE PANEL
quote: Listen to them! They're dying, Artoo! Curse my metal body! I wasn't fast enough. It's all my fault! My poor master!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN FORWARD BAY - SERVICE PANEL
quote: (over comlink) Threepio, we're all right!
We're all right. You did great.
Hey... hey, open the pressure maintenance hatch on unit number... where are we?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN FORWARD BAY - SERVICE PANEL
quote: (over comlink) Three-two-six-eight-two-seven.
If we can just avoid any more female advice, we ought to be able to get out of here.
Well, let's get moving!
(to Chewie) Where are you going?
No, wait. They'll hear!
(to Chewie) Come here, you big coward!
Chewie! Come here!
Listen. I don't know who you are, or where you came from, but from now on, you do as I tell you. Okay?
Look, Your Worshipfulness, let's get one thing straight! I take orders from one person! Me!
It's a wonder you're still alive. (looking at Chewie) Will somebody get this big walking carpet out of my way?
No reward is worth this.
(looking at his ship) There she is.
See-Threepio, do you copy?
(voice) For the moment. Uh, we're in the main hangar across from the ship.
We're right above you. Stand by.
You came in that thing? You're braver that I thought.
Nice! Come on!
(to Luke and Leia) Get back to the ship!
Where are you going? Come back!
He certainly has courage.
What good will it do us if he gets himself killed? Come on!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - CENTRAL CORE SHAFT
quote: (gasping) I think we took a wrong turn.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - CENTRAL CORE SHAFT
quote: There's no lock!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - CENTRAL CORE SHAFT
quote: That oughta hold it for a while.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - CENTRAL CORE SHAFT
quote: Quick, we've got to get across. Find the control that extends the bridge.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - CENTRAL CORE SHAFT
quote: Oh, I think I just blasted it.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - CENTRAL CORE SHAFT
quote: They're coming through!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - CENTRAL CORE SHAFT
quote: Here, hold this.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - CENTRAL CORE SHAFT
quote: Here they come!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - CENTRAL CORE SHAFT
quote: For luck!

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN FORWARD BAY
quote: Where could they be?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - HALLWAY LEADING TO MAIN FORWARD BAY
quote: I've been waiting for you, Obi-Wan. We meet again, at last. The circle is now complete.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - HALLWAY LEADING TO MAIN FORWARD BAY
quote: When I left you, I was but the learner; now I am the master.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - HALLWAY LEADING TO MAIN FORWARD BAY
quote: Only a master of evil, Darth.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - HALLWAY LEADING TO MAIN FORWARD BAY
quote: Your powers are weak, old man.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - HALLWAY LEADING TO MAIN FORWARD BAY
quote: You can't win, Darth. If you strike me down, I shall become more powerful than you can possibly imagine.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN FORWARD BAY
quote: Didn't we just leave this party?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN FORWARD BAY
quote: What kept you?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN FORWARD BAY
quote: We ran into some old friends.

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN FORWARD BAY
quote: Is the ship all right?

sceneTitle: INT. DEATH STAR - MAIN FORWARD BAY
quote: Seems okay, if we can get to it. Just hope the old man got the tractor beam out of commission.
Look!
Come on, Artoo, we're going!
Now's our chance! Go!
No!
(to Luke) Come on!
Come on! Luke, its too late!
Blast the door! Kid!
Run, Luke! Run!
I hope the old man got that tractor beam out if commission, or this is going to be a real short trip. Okay, hit it!
(to Chewie) We're coming up on the sentry ships. Hold 'em off! Angle the deflector shields while I charge up the main guns!

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: I can't believe he's gone.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: There wasn't anything you could have done.

sceneTitle: INT. MILLENNIUM FALCON - CENTRAL HOLD AREA
quote: (to Luke) Come on, buddy, we're not out of this yet!
(to Luke) You in, kid? Okay, stay sharp!
(into intercom) Here they come!
They're coming in too fast!
Oooh!
We've lost lateral controls.
Don't worry, she'll hold together.
(to ship) You hear me, baby? Hold together!
Got him! I got him!
Great kid! Don't get cocky.
There are still two more of them out there!
(laughing) That's it! We did it!
We did it!
Help! I think I'm melting! (to Artoo) This is all your fault.
Are they away?
They have just made the jump into hyperspace.
You're sure the homing beacon is secure aboard their ship? I'm taking an awful risk, Vader. This had better work.
Not a bad bit of rescuing, huh? You know, sometimes I even amaze myself.
That doesn't sound too hard. Besides, they let us go. It's the only explanation for the ease of our escape.
Easy... you call that easy?
Their tracking us!
Not this ship, sister.
At least the information in Artoo is still intact.
What's so important? What's he carrying?
The technical readouts of that battle station. I only hope that when the data is analyzed, a weakness can be found. It's not over yet!
It is for me, sister! Look, I ain't in this for your revolution, and I'm not in it for you, Princess. I expect to be well paid. I'm in it for the money!
You needn't worry about your reward. If money is all that you love, then that's what you'll receive!
Your friend is quite a mercenary. I wonder if he really cares about anything... or anyone.
I care!
So... what do you think of her, Han?
I'm trying not to, kid!
(under his breath) Good...
Still, she's got a lot of spirit. I don't know, what do you think? Do you think a princess and a guy like me...
No!

We don't have time for our sorrows, Commander. The battle station has surely tracked us here. (looking pointedly to Han) It's the only explanation for the ease of our escape. You must use the information in this R2 unit to plan the attack. It is our only hope.
Yes.

sceneTitle: INT. MASSASSI - WAR ROOM BRIEFING AREA
quote: It's not impossible. I used to bull's- eye womp rats in my T-sixteen back home. They're not much bigger than two meters.
This will be a day long remembered. It has seen the end of Kenobi and it will soon see the end of the Rebellion.

sceneTitle: INT. MASSASSI OUTPOST - MAIN HANGAR DECK
quote: So... you got your reward and you're just leaving then?

sceneTitle: INT. MASSASSI OUTPOST - MAIN HANGAR DECK
quote: That's right, yeah! I got some old debts I've got to pay off with this stuff. Even if I didn't, you don't think I'd be fool enough to stick around here, do you? Why don't you come with us? You're pretty good in a fight. I could use you.

sceneTitle: INT. MASSASSI OUTPOST - MAIN HANGAR DECK
quote: (getting angry) Come on! Why don't you take a look around? You know what's about to happen, what they're up against. They could use a good pilot like you. You're turning your back on them.

sceneTitle: INT. MASSASSI OUTPOST - MAIN HANGAR DECK
quote: What good's a reward if you ain't around to use it? Besides, attacking that battle station ain't my idea of courage. It's more like suicide.

sceneTitle: INT. MASSASSI OUTPOST - MAIN HANGAR DECK
quote: All right. Well, take care of yourself, Han. I guess that's what you're best at, isn't it?

sceneTitle: INT. MASSASSI OUTPOST - MAIN HANGAR DECK
quote: Hey, Luke... may the Force be with you!

sceneTitle: INT. MASSASSI OUTPOST - MAIN HANGAR DECK
quote: What're you lookin' at? I know what I'm doing.

sceneTitle: INT. MAIN HANGAR DECK - LUKE'S SHIP
quote: What's wrong?

sceneTitle: INT. MAIN HANGAR DECK - LUKE'S SHIP
quote: Oh, it's Han! I don't know, I really thought he'd change his mind.

sceneTitle: INT. MAIN HANGAR DECK - LUKE'S SHIP
quote: He's got to follow his own path. No one can choose it for him.

sceneTitle: INT. MAIN HANGAR DECK - LUKE'S SHIP
quote: I only wish Ben were here.

sceneTitle: INT. MAIN HANGAR DECK - LUKE'S SHIP
quote: Biggs! Of course, I'll be up there with you! Listen, have I got some stories to tell...

sceneTitle: INT. MAIN HANGAR DECK - LUKE'S SHIP
quote: Thank you, sir. I'll try.

sceneTitle: INT. MAIN HANGAR DECK - LUKE'S SHIP
quote: I told you I'd make it someday, Biggs.

sceneTitle: INT. MAIN HANGAR DECK - LUKE'S SHIP
quote: Not on your life! That little droid and I have been through a lot together. (to Artoo) You okay, Artoo?

sceneTitle: INT. MAIN HANGAR DECK - LUKE'S SHIP
quote: Hang on tight,Artoo, you've got to come back.

sceneTitle: INT. MAIN HANGAR DECK - LUKE'S SHIP
quote: You wouldn't want my life to get boring, would you?

sceneTitle: INT. MAIN HANGAR DECK - LUKE'S SHIP
quote: Luke, the Force will be with you.
Red Five standing by.
This is Red Five; I'm going in!
I got a little cooked, but I'm okay.
We'll have to destroy them ship to ship. Get the crews to their fighters.
I'm on my way in now...
I'm on it.
My scope's negative. I don't see anything.
Hang on, Biggs, I'm coming in.

sceneTitle: INT. LUKE'S X-WING FIGHTER - COCKPIT - TRAVELING
quote: Got him!
Several fighters have broken off from the main group. Come with me!
I'm hit, but not bad.
I can't shake him!
Blast it! Wedge where are you?
Thanks, Wedge.
Stay in attack formation!
I'll take them myself! Cover me!
Evacuate? In out moment of triumph? I think you overestimate their chances!
No sign of any... wait!
(over headset) Coming in point three five.
Close up formation.
(over headset) Red Leader, we're right above you. Turn to point...
...oh-five; we'll cover for you.
(over speaker) Biggs, Wedge, let's close it up. We're going in. We're going in full throttle.
It'll be just like Beggar's Canyon back home.
Watch yourself! Increase speed full throttle!
You worry about those fighters! I'll worry about the tower!
(to Artoo) Artoo... that, that stabilizer's broken loose again! See if you can't lock it down!
(over speaker) Get clear, Wedge.
You can't do any more good back there!
Let him go! Stay on the leader!
Artoo, try and increase the power!
I'm on the leader.
Hang on, Artoo!
Use the Force, Luke.
Let go, Luke.
The Force is strong with this one!
Luke, trust me.
(over speaker) Nothing. I'm all right.
I've lost Artoo!
You may fire when ready.
I have you now.
What?
(yelling) Yahoo!
(into mike) You're all clear, kid.
(over speaker) Now let's blow this thing and go home!
Great shot, kid. That was one in a million.
Remember, the Force will be with you... always.
Luke! Luke! Luke!
(laughing) Hey! Hey!
(laughing) I knew you'd come back! I just knew it!
Well, I wasn't gonna let you get all the credit and take all the reward.
(laughing) Hey, I knew there was more to you than money.
Oh, no!
Oh, my! Artoo! Can you hear me? Say something! (to mechanic) You can repair him, can't you?
You must repair him! Sir, if any of my circuits or gears will help, I'll gladly donate them.
He'll be all right.
